1
00:00:00,849 --> 00:00:04,430
Market structure should be the foundation
of your analysis.

2
00:00:04,430 --> 00:00:09,550
The first part of any trading plan is to establish
which side of the market is in the commanding

3
00:00:09,550 --> 00:00:12,830
position, buyers or sellers, demand or supply.

4
00:00:12,830 --> 00:00:17,630
Today we’ll talk about that, the market
structure and you’ll learn how to read charts

5
00:00:17,630 --> 00:00:18,870
correctly.

6
00:00:18,870 --> 00:00:25,620
So if you could like, subscribe to channel
and stick around for the full video.

7
00:00:25,620 --> 00:00:31,230
What is market structure
When reading market structure, you have to

8
00:00:31,230 --> 00:00:35,199
pay close attention to one thing on the chart:
price.

9
00:00:35,199 --> 00:00:37,290
Price will tell you all you need to know.

10
00:00:37,290 --> 00:00:42,309
When price is moving influenced by supply
and demand, this creates trends.

11
00:00:42,309 --> 00:00:46,899
A bull trend is depicted by higher highs (HH)
and higher lows (HL).

12
00:00:46,899 --> 00:00:51,789
The trend will continue in that direction
until a lower low is printed by the asset

13
00:00:51,789 --> 00:00:53,079
price.

14
00:00:53,079 --> 00:00:58,049
The trend begins to show signs of weakness
when it fails to print a higher high.

15
00:00:58,049 --> 00:01:03,839
A bear trend is the price action of lower
lows (LL) and lower highs (LH).

16
00:01:03,839 --> 00:01:09,450
The bear trend will continue to fall as long
as lower highs continue to print.

17
00:01:09,450 --> 00:01:13,520
Once a higher high comes into the price, the
trend will end.

18
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:18,680
The sign that the trend may be reversing is
when price begins to print higher lows or

19
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:20,820
equal lows.

20
00:01:20,820 --> 00:01:26,119
A sideways trend is a trend that has equal
highs and equal lows.

21
00:01:26,119 --> 00:01:31,299
Price trends in a range during this point
of the market and is in consolidation.

22
00:01:31,299 --> 00:01:34,460
Markets can move in a period of consolidation
for a long time.

23
00:01:34,460 --> 00:01:39,890
This trend is broken if the price breaks out
from the top or bottom of the range.

24
00:01:39,890 --> 00:01:43,420
This could be the beginning of one of the
first two trends.

25
00:01:43,420 --> 00:01:46,490
These are the obvious concepts regarding market
structure.

26
00:01:46,490 --> 00:01:49,542
Now let’s go deeper, and let me share the
subtleties of market structure.

27
00:01:49,542 --> 00:01:56,240
Price prints new high/low that breaks the
previous high/low

28
00:01:56,240 --> 00:02:02,079
The first principle is the most obvious one:
for a market to be in an active cycle, it’s

29
00:02:02,079 --> 00:02:07,609
most recent structure must be one where price
prints a high that breaks the previous high

30
00:02:07,609 --> 00:02:10,460
(this is the case of a bullish cycle).

31
00:02:10,460 --> 00:02:16,050
A down-cycle will be established if the latest
swing low in price breaks below the most recent

32
00:02:16,050 --> 00:02:17,050
low.

33
00:02:17,050 --> 00:02:23,420
In this hourly chart, you can clearly see
the market in an up-cycle phase on higher

34
00:02:23,420 --> 00:02:25,550
highs and higher lows.

35
00:02:25,550 --> 00:02:33,570
Several Closes Beyond Last High/Low
To confirm that a bullish trend or up-cycle

36
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:38,920
is evolving in a healthy manner, not only
we need to see the high printed being higher

37
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:44,510
than its previous high, but we also should
expect at least several closes above that

38
00:02:44,510 --> 00:02:50,420
high or support area, as further evidence
that the market is accepting and building

39
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:51,730
value.

40
00:02:51,730 --> 00:02:57,430
Failure to print at least two or three closes
above that high may translate into a false

41
00:02:57,430 --> 00:03:03,400
breakout, and while the move still holds its
merit to qualify as a new high in the cycle,

42
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:06,310
the quality of the leg is poor in nature.

43
00:03:06,310 --> 00:03:14,320
Find confirmation from higher time frames
You must avoid the trap of being short-sighted

44
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:17,480
by only sticking to one chart analysis.

45
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:22,620
When conducting your market structure analysis,
it’s all about finding confirmation from

46
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:27,020
higher time frames down to your trading time
frame.

47
00:03:27,020 --> 00:03:32,820
What this means is that if you are going to
find an entry trigger on the hourly time frame,

48
00:03:32,820 --> 00:03:37,801
you should then understand what type of conditions
are dominant in the immediately higher time

49
00:03:37,801 --> 00:03:38,940
frames.

50
00:03:38,940 --> 00:03:44,320
The most popular in this case would be the
4h and daily charts.

51
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:51,750
50% retracement rule
A major mistake made by traders when analyzing

52
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:57,310
market structure is allowing too much guessing
play a role in their analysis.

53
00:03:57,310 --> 00:04:02,720
When analyzing the charts, how do you determine
a relevant swing high/low?

54
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:05,540
Is it this one, or this one?

55
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:06,900
Which is more relevant?

56
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:11,400
That’s why you need to find a mechanical
approach that will allow you to qualify a

57
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:14,540
relevant swing high or swing low in the chart.

58
00:04:14,540 --> 00:04:22,100
Here’s my general rule, if a swing low/high
doesn’t make it to at least the 50% retracement

59
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:28,510
of its previous swing, I disregard that price
movement as not relevant enough to represent

60
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:29,550
a valid leg.

61
00:04:29,550 --> 00:04:36,290
I only want to focus on the creation of relevant
and valid legs that will lead to new cycles

62
00:04:36,290 --> 00:04:40,500
and create in the process relevant levels
of supports and resistances.

63
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:43,510
We’ll talk about this later.

64
00:04:43,510 --> 00:04:50,500
Transitions From Trends To Ranges
Market don’t always trend, and you’ll

65
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:55,720
come to the point in the market structure
where the dominant trend starts drying up,

66
00:04:55,720 --> 00:05:02,200
maybe due to increased profit-taking, removals
of liquidity, intervention by market-makers

67
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:04,980
or economic data-driven moves.

68
00:05:04,980 --> 00:05:09,971
While in an up-cycle, the interpretation of
the market structure is straightforward, you

69
00:05:09,971 --> 00:05:13,880
must determine when you’ve transitioned
from a trend into a consolidation.

70
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:14,900
Here’s my method.

71
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:18,680
We’ll cover an uptrend transitioning into
consolidation.

72
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:22,900
Firstly, you must see a failed test of a valid
high.

73
00:05:22,900 --> 00:05:25,600
Price is unable to break the recent high.

74
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:31,590
Secondly, a failed test of the most recent
swing low would confirm that we have entered

75
00:05:31,590 --> 00:05:38,780
a consolidation phase, which would last until
the most recent valid high or low is broken,

76
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:42,860
with at several closes above/below the level.

77
00:05:42,860 --> 00:05:49,490
In this context, don’t forget that the consolidation
is within the context of an up-cycle.

78
00:05:49,490 --> 00:05:56,050
Until sellers manage to break and hold below
the latest valid swing low, the strength remains

79
00:05:56,050 --> 00:05:57,620
to the upside.

80
00:05:57,620 --> 00:06:05,280
Magnitude of the Cycle
Another major sign that will help us determine

81
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:11,310
the health of the cycle is the type of progress
made by the dominant side in control of the

82
00:06:11,310 --> 00:06:12,310
cycle.

83
00:06:12,310 --> 00:06:17,990
You need to ask the following question: Are
the new legs in the cycle increasing or decreasing

84
00:06:17,990 --> 00:06:19,760
in magnitude?

85
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:26,639
Here, despite having entered a period of consolidation
in the hourly chart, if we measure the latest

86
00:06:26,639 --> 00:06:32,650
swing high, if we measure its extension from
the last low to the newly established high,

87
00:06:32,650 --> 00:06:37,200
we see that this is a bigger advance vs the
previous up leg.

88
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:43,480
This means that buyers are increasing their
commitment on each new cycle high (greater

89
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:50,710
demand imbalances), therefore, this is yet
another clue that the strength is to the upside.

90
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:58,490
Velocity of the Cycle
When it comes to the distance the price moves,

91
00:06:58,490 --> 00:07:01,330
the magnitude is only half of the equation.

92
00:07:01,330 --> 00:07:06,130
The other one has to do with the velocity
of the move or the speed.

93
00:07:06,130 --> 00:07:10,870
Was the new leg created after a fast and impulsive
move?

94
00:07:10,870 --> 00:07:16,830
Or did price make a new low or high with the
movement being sluggish, compressive and taking

95
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:18,550
too long to form?

96
00:07:18,550 --> 00:07:24,300
A good rule of thumb is to count the approximate
number of candles it took to achieve a new

97
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:25,300
leg.

98
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:31,270
In this case, you can see that the second
leg was created with a lower number of candles.

99
00:07:31,270 --> 00:07:32,900
At a faster speed.

100
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:35,681
So the cycle continues to prosper in a healthy
manner.

101
00:07:35,681 --> 00:07:44,510
Projection Targets In A New Cycle
A reliable measure I have found to set targets

102
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:50,800
when trading cycles is to measure the 100%
Fibonacci projection from the most recent

103
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:53,190
valid swing low to its high.

104
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:58,710
In Tradingview, you use this tool, Trend-based
FIB Extension.

105
00:07:58,710 --> 00:08:04,490
You need to join the lowest, the highest point
and the low of the retracement or the pullback

106
00:08:04,490 --> 00:08:05,949
as the third point.

107
00:08:05,949 --> 00:08:10,900
For example, looking at this chart, we are
in an up cycle.

108
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:17,910
The first point to draw the Fibonacci extension
would be at point A, the point B will be here

109
00:08:17,910 --> 00:08:22,770
and the third point will be here, at the low
of the retracement.

110
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:29,090
This will give you the 100% Fibonacci projection,
and other probable resistance levels where

111
00:08:29,090 --> 00:08:32,890
the price may face resistance in the near
future.

112
00:08:32,890 --> 00:08:38,779
If the cycle continues in the expected direction,
you will start to appreciate the power and

113
00:08:38,779 --> 00:08:44,930
usefulness of these targets to consider taking
profits or trailing stops, in the hope of

114
00:08:44,930 --> 00:08:47,209
a larger profit for your trade.

115
00:08:47,209 --> 00:08:54,670
In this example, notice how this target was
reached almost to the pip before buyers took

116
00:08:54,670 --> 00:08:55,889
profit.

117
00:08:55,889 --> 00:09:03,300
Cluster Of Levels Nearby
Another important exercise you must perform

118
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:09,250
is to draw the most immediate lines of support
and resistance — at least 2 up and 2 down

119
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:12,420
— based on a top-down analysis.

120
00:09:12,420 --> 00:09:14,160
They should be obvious to spot.

121
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:19,390
Here you must take into account:
- the number of times the area has been tested

122
00:09:19,390 --> 00:09:25,029
(ideally, minimum 2 times),
- the type of reaction away from this area

123
00:09:25,029 --> 00:09:31,680
(the stronger the more relevant),
- time frame (the higher the timeframe, the

124
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:33,980
more significant the level is).

125
00:09:33,980 --> 00:09:40,129
Here, I’ve drawn the two most immediate
levels of support and resistance in the daily

126
00:09:40,129 --> 00:09:42,050
and H4.

127
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:48,170
What this means is that if you are going to
find trades on the H1 chart, you must be aware

128
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:53,709
that once the price reaches these areas in
the higher time frames, a potential reaction

129
00:09:53,709 --> 00:10:00,110
in the structure in your trading time frame
(H1 in our example) may occur, so you must

130
00:10:00,110 --> 00:10:04,279
be aware by anticipating this potential outcome.

131
00:10:04,279 --> 00:10:10,929
Marking these levels in your chart allows
you to know when to expect a potential reversal.

132
00:10:10,929 --> 00:10:15,809
If you’ve followed me this far, you now
understand that a new cycle would be confirmed

133
00:10:15,809 --> 00:10:20,230
if we can break and have several closes outside
a range.

134
00:10:20,230 --> 00:10:26,610
However, what if we break the current range
but we are faced with another recent low immediately

135
00:10:26,610 --> 00:10:27,899
ahead?

136
00:10:27,899 --> 00:10:33,680
If the distance is relatively narrow, a safer
approach is to wait until a breakout of the

137
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:39,100
most distant level in that cluster of support
areas, which would be several closes below

138
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:43,020
this second level, to confirm the down cycle.

139
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:48,779
Essentially, when this situation occurs, what
you probably want to do is to expand the size

140
00:10:48,779 --> 00:10:51,860
of the range and wait for a resolution outside.

141
00:10:51,860 --> 00:11:00,540
How to trade market structure
So, how can you go about trading these cycles?

142
00:11:00,540 --> 00:11:04,999
• First , assuming you are trading off the
hourly chart, you want to make sure to trade

143
00:11:04,999 --> 00:11:11,220
also in line with at least the immediately
higher timeframe cycle (H4), and ideally both

144
00:11:11,220 --> 00:11:13,849
(daily and H4).

145
00:11:13,849 --> 00:11:19,160
• You also want to double-check that the
hourly market structure is trending, several

146
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:25,599
closes beyond the last valid swing low/high
to confirm a new leg in the cycle.

147
00:11:25,599 --> 00:11:31,029
• It’s important that you then check the
absence of nearby cluster levels from higher

148
00:11:31,029 --> 00:11:37,019
time frames or economic data releases that
may disturb the structure.

149
00:11:37,019 --> 00:11:43,220
• And pay attention to both the magnitude
and the speed on the creation of a new cycle.

150
00:11:43,220 --> 00:11:49,920
If we are in a healthy cycle with lower lows
for example, decent magnitude moves and no

151
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:56,550
obstruction of higher timeframe levels, pay
attention to the 50% fib retracement of the

152
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:57,550
correction.

153
00:11:57,550 --> 00:12:03,149
The 50% fib retracement a great location to
start looking for trades based on your ideal

154
00:12:03,149 --> 00:12:04,410
entry technique.

155
00:12:04,410 --> 00:12:10,910
Some traders may prefer to set limit orders
at this levels with a stop a few pips away

156
00:12:10,910 --> 00:12:13,470
from the most recent high.

157
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:19,509
Others may prefer a confirmation trigger such
as the break of a trendline, a particular

158
00:12:19,509 --> 00:12:28,300
pattern (flag, triangle etc) or a specific
price action formation such as engulfing bars,

159
00:12:28,300 --> 00:12:29,839
pin bars.

160
00:12:29,839 --> 00:12:35,230
Whichever way you approach your trades, the
area you are looking to trade from must hold

161
00:12:35,230 --> 00:12:40,429
value on the basis of decent risk-reward prospects.

162
00:12:40,429 --> 00:12:43,430
You can alter the entry approach as you wish.

163
00:12:43,430 --> 00:12:50,019
I personally like to find entries at the 50%
fib retracement, but you can also wait for

164
00:12:50,019 --> 00:13:02,990
entries at the area between 50 - 61.8%, also
known as the golden zone or at 78.6% fib retracements.

165
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:09,069
In fact, a great pattern for a potentially
large risk-reward is to be on the lookout

166
00:13:09,069 --> 00:13:16,619
to trade a retracement at the 78.6% Fibonacci
within the context of a strong and healthy

167
00:13:16,619 --> 00:13:17,670
cycle.

168
00:13:17,670 --> 00:13:26,699
These trades tend to offer the best opportunities,
with a narrow stop and a larger profit potential.

169
00:13:26,699 --> 00:13:33,439
Fibonacci extensions are a great way to establish
price targets or find projected areas of support

170
00:13:33,439 --> 00:13:39,209
or resistance, when the price is moving into
an area where other methods of finding support

171
00:13:39,209 --> 00:13:41,839
or resistance are not so evident.

172
00:13:41,839 --> 00:13:47,889
If you are long on a trade for example, and
a new high occurs, you can use the Fibonacci

173
00:13:47,889 --> 00:13:51,730
extension levels for an idea of where the
price may go.

174
00:13:51,730 --> 00:13:56,360
You have the option to decide whether to cover
the position at that level.

175
00:13:56,360 --> 00:14:05,389
I prefer the 100% Fib projection and the next
important one is at 1.618 level.

176
00:14:05,389 --> 00:14:08,490
This is the simplest way of analyzing a market.

177
00:14:08,490 --> 00:14:15,459
The big advantage in analyzing market structure
this way consists is keeping your charts clean,

178
00:14:15,459 --> 00:14:19,499
uncluttered, away from unnecessary indicators.

179
00:14:19,499 --> 00:14:24,980
And of course, some degree of subjectivity
will always be required.

180
